channel.title: What is wrong? {Not helped yet} - Helper gets rep++
channel.description:
Hi, I followed this tut: http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,295157.0.html
...And I got this error when I compile: [code]client.java:1537: illegal start of expression public boolean AttackNPC() { ^ 1 error
AdvancedScape Is Now Compiled.
Druk op een toets om door te gaan. . .[/code]
Where is the error located? And how do I fix it?
Thanks in advance, Allard

item.title: What is wrong? {Not helped yet} - Helper gets rep++
item.dc:creator: @bryanc Bryanc
item.description:
@bryanc wrote:

No, just no…

@Allardx

Delete that bracket on the line 1521. It was an extra bracket because you added a closing bracket to close the method. Then there was still one from the original closing bracket. (You put a method inside of another method, then added a new closing bracket to close the method. Then the original was left)
